news.title: Collection of property tax stays suspended in areas merged with Pune civic body
news.para: Urban Development Minister Madhuri Misal clarified that property tax collection in Pune's merged areas remains suspended, addressing concerns raised by MLA Bhimrao Tapkir regarding inflated bills and discrepancies compared to previous panchayat charges. While some residents paid voluntarily, the government has directed PMC to revise the tax structure proposal.

news.title: Telangana RERA fines BhuvanTeza for selling unregistered project
news.para: TG RERA fined BhuvanTeza Infra Projects ₹6.45 lakh for failing to register 'Happy Homes-1' in Shamirpet, marketed between 2020-2023. Buyers, including Appam Kiran Kumar, alleged aggressive pre-launch promotions and false assurances. The developer must refund principal amounts with 11% interest within 90 days due to stalled project and lack of approvals.

news.title: Telangana RERA penalizes Ashritha Group for real estate violations in Jubilee Hills
news.para: Telangana RERA has directed Ashritha Group to register two residential flats in favour of homebuyers, Srinivasulu Bode and C Malleswari Nandireddy, who complained about the builder's failure to honor agreement terms for flats in 'Jewels County'.

news.title: Cement sector set for 30–80% profit surge
news.para: Cement producers are poised to report substantial profit increases for the June quarter, driven by improved prices and volumes, particularly in East and South India. Despite early monsoon rains impacting volume growth, the industry witnessed the highest average cement prices since December 2023. While near-term margins may peak, consolidation is expected to continue within the sector.

news.title: Lucknow development body to e-auction 50 plots, two commercial complexes
news.para: Lucknow Development Authority plans e-auction of 50 residential plots in Basant Kunj Scheme. Two major commercial complexes are also listed. Plots are in Sector-G near Gau Ghat. A 2.5-hectare plot near SSB in Gomti Nagar Extension is selected. Commercial plots in Vishal Khand, Gomtinagar are listed too. Authority plans high-rise residential buildings on LDA-owned land near Balu Adda and Bhadeva.

news.title: DDA schedules meeting for auction of Rohini warehouse land parcel
news.para: The Delhi Development Authority (DDA) is set to auction a 23-acre land parcel in Rohini, Sector 36, for a large-scale warehousing complex, marking their first venture into this type of development. DDA aims to discourage warehouse purchases in NCR regions by offering the property through a 33-year licensing agreement with an annual fee of Rs 17.4 crore.

news.title: Mohali: Court orders Parkview Residences' upkeep handover to RWA
news.para: The SDM court in Mohali has ordered Bestech developers to transfer maintenance responsibilities of Parkview Residences to the resident welfare association (PVRAOWA) by July 23, resolving a long-standing dispute. This decision empowers the RWA, legally formed under the Punjab Apartment Ownership Act, to manage the society's upkeep, ending the developer's control and alleged harassment of residents.

news.title: Punjab RERA restrains Motiaz from booking, selling flats
news.para: Rera Punjab has prohibited Motiaz, a Chandigarh-based builder, from advertising, marketing, or selling flats in 'The Royale Sector 39 Extension' in Mohali due to non-registration with Rera. The developer failed to respond to multiple notices, violating Section 3 of the RERA Act.

news.title: Chennai development body's portal glitch causes delays for homebuyers
news.para: Chennai homebuyers are facing potential possession delays due to technical glitches and approval backlogs within the CMDA portal. Developers report issues with uploading project files, sanction plan delays, and prolonged processing of Completion Certificates, especially for high-rise buildings.

news.title: Goldman Sachs finances $270 million affordable housing project in New York
news.para: Goldman Sachs is set to finance a $270 million affordable housing project in Brooklyn's East New York, aiming to construct 385 apartments with commercial space. This initiative addresses the city's housing crisis, a key focus of mayoral candidate Zohran Mamdani's campaign.

news.title: Union home minister chairs high-level meeting on Delhi master plan 2041
news.para: Union Home Minister Amit Shah led a high-level meeting to assess the Delhi Master Plan 2041, with Delhi Chief Minister Rekha Gupta and Union Minister Manohar Lal Khattar participating. The meeting, following a prior review, addressed the plan submitted by the DDA in April 2023, which is still awaiting final approval after receiving the LG's endorsement.

news.title: PropShare Titania SM REIT ₹473 crore issue to open on July 21
news.para: Property Share Investment Trust has introduced PropShare Titania, their second SM REIT scheme, aiming to raise up to ₹473 crore. The IPO, featuring a fresh issue of units priced between ₹10 lakh and ₹10.6 lakh, will be open for subscription from July 21 to July 25, 2025.

news.title: UK's Barratt Redrow misses home completion target, warns of 'fragile' buyer confidence
news.para: Barratt Redrow, Britain's largest homebuilder, faced a setback as it missed its annual home completion forecast, reporting 16,565 completions against the projected 16,800-17,200. This shortfall, coupled with fragile buyer confidence amid a faltering economy, sent the company's shares plummeting. The London market proved particularly weak, impacting overall performance.

news.title: The Executive Centre is said to seek ₹2,600 crore for India IPO
news.para: The Executive Centre is planning an initial public offering in Mumbai that may raise 26 billion rupees ($303 million), according to people familiar with the matter, to capitalize on the rising demand for workspace in the country.

news.title: Karnataka CM says government will stop land acquisition for an aerospace park
news.para: The CM, after a long discussion with the farmer leaders, said the government, however, was open to buying land from farmers open to giving their land up for industrial use. Such farmers would get higher compensation than the guidance value or a higher share of developed land as compensation, he added.

news.title: Commercial assets account for 62% of ₹6,500 crore real estate deals in Q2 2025
news.para: India's real estate sector experienced a slowdown in Q2 2025, with deal value declining to USD 775 million. Despite the drop in overall volumes, commercial development remained strong, driven by significant investments like Blackstone's acquisition of South City Mall. Capital markets showed signs of recovery, and investor sentiment leans towards larger, yield-focused investments.

news.title: Villagers oppose proposed cement plant in Mansa village
news.para: Residents of Talwandi Aklia and Karamgarh Autanwali protested against a proposed cement plant. The Punjab Pollution Control Board held a public hearing. Villagers fear environmental hazards from the red category industry. The Public Action Committee mobilized the opposition. JSW Cement Limited plans a 6 MTPA plant. Concerns were raised about the project's impact.

news.title: Karnataka: Note to urban development department offers hope to B khata property owners
news.para: The note is based on a letter written by former president of BJP Bengaluru South NR Ramesh. “Most of the buildings are constructed on B khata properties.

news.title: Belagavi civic body collects record ₹44.7 crore property tax in Q1 FY26
news.para: Belagavi City Corporation targets Rs 75 crore in property tax for fiscal year 2025-26. The corporation collected Rs 44.7 crore in the first quarter. This was due to a 5% rebate scheme. The BCC focuses on unauthorized buildings and tax defaulters. Owners of unlawful constructions must pay a single tax. The corporation has initiated recovery measures for chronic defaulters.
